
## Quickstart (5 min)

### Step 1: Clone the Repository

Open your terminal and run:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Ikalus1988/MisakaNet.git
cd MisakaNet
```

### Step 2: Install Dependencies

MisakaNet requires Python 3.10+ and no additional dependencies beyond the Python standard library. Ensure you have Python installed:

```bash
python3 --version
```

### Step 3: Run Your First Search

Execute the following command to run a search:

```bash
python3 search_knowledge.py "pip install timeout"
```

### Step 4: Understand the Output

The output will display the most relevant lessons related to your query. For example:

```bash
  ✅ [0.85] pip install timeout
      → matched: DCO sign-off fails on Windows
  💡 View full content: cat lessons/contrib/dco-auto-fix-workflow.md
  💡 Contribute new knowledge: python3 scripts/queue_lesson.py -t 'title' -d domain 'content...'
```

This indicates that the search found a relevant lesson with a high confidence score. You can view the full content of the lesson by running the provided `cat` command or contribute new knowledge using the `queue_lesson.py` script.

